Republishing on Localized Platforms:
- You may translate mod descriptions and repost them on local platforms, provided:
  - The repost is marked as unofficial and not associated with the author.
  - No mod files are re-uploaded; link to original uploads on the author’s official project pages.
  - The repost is non-commercial, with no direct or indirect monetary gain or purpose.
    This includes, but is not limited to, monetization through advertisements, subscriptions, donations, or any other revenue-generating mechanisms.
    For example, using translated mod descriptions on a platform with paid access or ad revenue is considered commercial use and is prohibited.

Republishing Mod Files:
- Publicly reuploading, rehosting, or distributing mod files is prohibited.
- You are allowed to make changes to the mod files if you are not publishing them publicly, i.e. they are only shared with your friends, family, or community.
- If you have made changes to the mod, you must make your users aware that they are using a modified version of the mod.

